aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 20, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104awp1665702772857.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/awp1665702772857.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/awp1665702772857.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"awp1665702772857\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Write Script Worksheet\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"awp1665702772857__write_script_worksheet_21440\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Write Script Worksheet enables you to write ProcScript and JavaScript, and to edit objects shown in the Structure.\n </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"awp1665702772857__li_d2327e1_d2328e1_d2329e1\">In the Entity Editor, you can write generic ProcScript for controlling data I/O or common application behavior.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"awp1665702772857__li_d2330e1_d2331e1_d2332e1\">In the Component Editor, you can code component-specific behavior for the component and its entities, occurrences, and fields.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"awp1665702772857__li_d2333e1_d2334e1_d2335e1\">In Library editors, you can define IncludeScript and Global ProcScript modules and Snippets.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"awp1665702772857__p_d5291e1_d5292e1_d5293e1\">The code that is ultimately compiled in a component may come from several sources:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"awp1665702772857__li_d2336e1_d2337e1_d2338e1\">Locally-defined script written in the code containers of the component and its entities and fields\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"awp1665702772857__li_d2339e1_d2340e1_d2341e1\">Inherited script, defined in modeled entities and fields used by the component\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"awp1665702772857__li_d2342e1_d2343e1_d2344e1\">Generated script, coming from IncludeScript that is resolved during compilation\n </li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"awp1665702772857__topic_d2782e1_d2783e1_d2784e1_d2785e1_d2786e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d150793e80\">\n                  \n Tools\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"awp1665702772857__li_d2345e1_d2346e1_d2347e1\">Resource Browser—depending on the editor, you add objects to the Structure using the Templates and Model tabs, or copy code from the Snippets tab.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"awp1665702772857__li_d2348e1_d2349e1_d2350e1\">Script Editor—enables you to navigate to and edit up to two code containers simultaneously.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"awp1665702772857__li_d2351e1_d2352e1_d2353e1\">Compiled Modules Inspector—provides a summary of the ProcScript modules for the selected object after compilation, and enables you to navigate to the module declaration, whether it is inherited, generated, or locally-defined.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"awp1665702772857__topic_d2787e1_d2788e1_d2789e1_d2790e1_d2791e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d150793e99\">\n                  \n How to\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"awp1665702772857__li_d2354e1_d2355e1_d2356e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yhf1665702772928.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yhf1665702772928.html\" title=\"You can search for a string or replace a string in the code editor in the Uniface IDE using the IDE code editor popup menu.\">Find and Replace Strings in Code</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"awp1665702772857__li_d2357e1_d2358e1_d2359e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wla1665702773104.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wla1665702773104.html\" title=\"The Write Script worksheet allows you to open two views of the Script Editor, each with its own Structure pane and Code Editor.\">Split Views in the Script Editor</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"awp1665702772857__li_d2360e1_d2361e1_d2362e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ouo1665702763029.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ouo1665702763029.html\" title=\"To navigate directly to the script modules of a development object, double-click the object (such as a field, entity, or component) in any worksheet for a modeled entity or component. This opens the Write Script worksheet at the selected object.\">Navigate to ProcScript modules</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"awp1665702772857__li_d2363e1_d2364e1_d2365e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qle1665702773192.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qle1665702773192.html\" title=\"Use the Uniface IDE to develop an application, following the Uniface development paradigm of Model, Construct, Build, and Deploy.\">Using the Uniface IDE</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"awp1665702772857__li_d2366e1_d2367e1_d2368e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dkp1665702773261.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dkp1665702773261.html\" title=\"Although development objects can be quite different in content and purpose, the way you create, edit and delete them in the Uniface IDE is essentially the same.\">Working with Development Objects</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kvf1665702667063.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Scripting Application Behavior</a><p>Uniface enables you to script application behavior using ProcScript, Uniface's own scripting language, and JavaScript, the most widely-used scripting language for web applications.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/biv1704450635249.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Snippets</a><p>Snippets are named fragments of code or text that you can insert into your application script or layout to speed development. They are defined as development objects in snippet libraries.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/byr1665702625184.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Compiled Module Information</a><p>The Compiled Module Inspector in the Write Script worksheet provides insight into the code that is available in the runtime component. It displays a summary of the compiled modules and their sources.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525902\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525902\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Write Script Worksheet Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Write Script Worksheet The Write Script Worksheet enables you to write ProcScript and JavaScript, and to edit objects shown in the Structure. In the Entity Editor, you can write generic ProcScript for controlling data I/O or common application behavior. In the Component Editor, you can code component-specific behavior for the component and its entities, occurrences, and fields. In Library editors, you can define IncludeScript and Global ProcScript modules and Snippets. The code that is ultimately compiled in a component may come from several sources: Locally-defined script written in the code containers of the component and its entities and fields Inherited script, defined in modeled entities and fields used by the component Generated script, coming from IncludeScript that is resolved during compilation Tools Resource Browser—depending on the editor, you add objects to the Structure using the Templates and Model tabs, or copy code from the Snippets tab. Script Editor—enables you to navigate to and edit up to two code containers simultaneously. Compiled Modules Inspector—provides a summary of the ProcScript modules for the selected object after compilation, and enables you to navigate to the module declaration, whether it is inherited, generated, or locally-defined. How to Find and Replace Strings in Code Split Views in the Script Editor Navigate to ProcScript modules Using the Uniface IDE Working with Development Objects Related Links Scripting Application Behavior Uniface enables you to script application behavior using ProcScript, Uniface's own scripting language, and JavaScript, the most widely-used scripting language for web applications. Snippets Snippets are named fragments of code or text that you can insert into your application script or layout to speed development. They are defined as development objects in snippet libraries. Compiled Module Information The Compiled Module Inspector in the Write Script worksheet provides insight into the code that is available in the runtime component. It displays a summary of the compiled modules and their sources. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}